               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate notBefore="1820" notAfter="1825">, according to
                       <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1071dAbbadi">Antoine d'Abbadie</persName>.</origDate>
                     The manuscript is of unusually small size and written in
                     microscript. According to <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1071dAbbadi">Antoine d'Abbadie</persName>, it
                     was meant as an amulet, for carrying on the chest.</origin>
                  <provenance>The manuscript belonged to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS13425Fanta">Fantā</persName> and was given by him to
                    <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1071dAbbadi">Antoine d'Abbadie</persName> as gift
                    in <date>1842/1843 CE</date>.</provenance>
                  <acquisition>The manuscript entered the Bibliothèque nationale in
                    <date>1902</date>.
                    </acquisition>
               </history>
